    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>Welcome to <strong>KBDS (Kaun Banega Dharma Shiromani)</strong> – a fun and educational game designed to promote and teach the fundamentals and advanced concepts of Jainism. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our game.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We do not collect any personally identifiable information (PII) unless explicitly provided by the user. However, we may collect the following information to enhance your experience:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Game Progress Data:</strong> Level reached, questions attempted, scores, and stage (Beginner, Expert).</li>
      <li><strong>Login Information:</strong> When users log in using a mobile number or email, we may securely store authentication-related data (such as login time and method) to facilitate user access and maintain personalized gameplay experience.</li>
      <li><strong>Usage Stats:</strong> Anonymous metrics like time spent in the game, popular features, and lifeline usage.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To provide and enhance your gameplay experience.</li>
      <li>To manage leaderboards and highlight top scores.</li>
      <li>To improve game features and customize content.</li>
      <li>To fix bugs and analyze performance.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><em>Your data will never be used for marketing or advertisements.</em></p>

    <h2>3. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>We do not sell or rent user data. Information may be shared only in the following cases:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> For storage, analytics, or maintenance with strict confidentiality.</li>
      <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> When required by law or legal process.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>KBDS is suitable for all ages, including children. We follow laws to protect kids' privacy. No personal data is knowingly collected from children under 13. If a parent believes their child submitted info, they may contact us to remove it.</p>

    <h2>5. Security</h2>
    <p>We use standard security practices to protect user data. However, no system is completely secure, so we can't guarantee absolute protection.</p>

    <h2>6. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy over time. Any changes will be posted here. Continuing to use the game after changes means you accept the updated policy.</p>


    <p>Thank you for playing KBDS and helping share Jain teachings in a fun and engaging way!</p>
